sources.description:
SILKEN STOCKING! ROARING SIX-GUNS!...in the west's most-roaring town!
Marshall Dan Mitchell, who is the law in Abilene, has the job of keeping peace. For a long time, the town had been divided, it made things easier for him, and kept problems from arising between the two factions.

Original title: Abilene Town (1946)

Colorized version: https://youtu.be/B4KqVObVLO8

Director: Edwin L. Marin
Writers: Ernest Haycox, Harold Shumate 
Stars: Randolph Scott, Ann Dvorak, Edgar Buchanan & Lloyd Bridges
Genre: Western
